<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-11-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="216" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d216">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. F. W. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Blair</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 5.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-11-05"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 5, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            dispatch No. 2, of the 10th ultimo.</p>
                        <p>Your proceedings as described since your arrival in the republic are
                            approved. Your cordial reception by its government, and the very
                            friendly remarks made on that occasion by the President, are extremely
                            gratifying.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F. W. SEWARD, <hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Jacob B. Blair</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>